<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-06-30T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-06-30T11:00:00-05:00" n="367" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d367">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.00111 Lic. <hi rend="superscript">Douglas/52</hi> Aircraft Co. Inc./5: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Counselor of Embassy in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-06-30T12:00:00-04:00">June 30,
                                1938—noon</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>454. Your no. 991, June 28, 5 p.m. The laws prohibiting the exportation
                            of arms to Spain contain no provisions under which exceptions to the
                            prohibition could be granted.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>